# Rush publish-time registry — used by: rush publish --publish
#
# `rush publish` WITHOUT --publish is a dry run (it never releases), and
# NPM_AUTH_TOKEN is only read at publish time, so there is no "accidental
# release" path here — you must opt in explicitly.
#
# Set NPM_AUTH_TOKEN in your environment (or CI secrets) before a real publish.
#
# For a local Verdaccio dry run, override the registry at call time instead of
# hardcoding a scope override here:
#   rush publish --publish --registry http://localhost:4873
registry=https://registry.npmjs.org/
//registry.npmjs.org/:_authToken=${NPM_AUTH_TOKEN}
//localhost:4873/:_authToken=${NPM_AUTH_TOKEN}
